Mennel Milling Co. has performed hazard evaluations for the chlorination processes at the facility.  As a result of this evaluation, several changes are planned to improve safety.  These changes, to be implemented by the end of 1999, include:
7 Installation of chlorine gas detectors to sense a leak and to alert employees;
7 Establishment of a procedure to minimize the potential for accidents during unloading of full chlorine containers;
7 Labeling of chlorine pipes.
